cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to solve the problem of moving object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes an extension of a state-of-the-art batch MOD method using unsupervised and generative neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also uses optimization techniques, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with video sequences, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique used in neural networks, and hence, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category.
